      "type": "progress note",
      "description": "Documents urgent office visit for 21-year-old male presenting with classic measles prodrome (cough, coryza, conjunctivitis) followed by high fever and cephalocaudal maculopapular rash. Koplik spots identified. Airborne isolation initiated. Labs ordered including measles IgM, measles PCR, CBC, CMP, CRP. Diagnosis of measles confirmed. Supportive care with acetaminophen and vitamin A prescribed. Reportable disease notification filed."
    },
    {
      "type": "public health case report",
      "description": "Mandatory reportable disease notification filed same day to Public Health Madison & Dane County and Wisconsin Department of Health Services per Wisconsin Statute § 252. Includes patient demographics, clinical presentation, lab confirmatory results, travel history (Manila, Philippines, March 7–15), estimated infectious period (March 19–27, 2026), and campus exposure locations. State case ID: WI-MEAS-2026-0047."
    },
    {
      "type": "patient instructions",
      "description": "Written instructions provided to patient regarding airborne isolation requirements, expected clinical course of measles, oral rehydration guidance, and return precautions (worsening respiratory distress, altered mental status, persistent high fever beyond day 4 of rash). Includes isolation duration through March 27, 2026 and telehealth follow-up scheduled for March 26."
